<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4593935>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figure 2. (A–D) Zyzzogeton guatemalensis sp. nov., male holotype. (A) Pygofer, subgenital plate, and anal tube, lateral view. (B) Genital capsule, ventral view. (C) Connective and style, dorsal view. (D) Aedeagus, lateral view. (E–G) Zyzzogeton haenschi Breddin, female. (E) Abdominal sternite VII, ventral view. (F) Pygofer and anal tube, lateral view. (G) Second valvula of ovipositor, general lateral view. BHA: basal hyaline area, RPL: subrectangular pygofer lobe. (Scale bars: 1 mm.)" ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4593935/files/figure.png" .

